      "message": "cc\u003dvmiura@\n\nVictor- this makes the idea we discussed possible where we draw *every* stroke with 64 segments. When I experimented with drawing the \"paths\" benchmark this way, the GPU itself rendered the whole scene in 1.5ms (as compared to .7ms with tessellation). Since the CPU takes 5.2ms, non-tessellation looks like it will still be 4.5x faster than the frame rate bottleneck.",
